# AI-assisted development guidelines for Cursor IDE users

## Composer Behavior
- Frontend components: prefer functional components with hooks over class components
- When generating new flow nodes, extend `BaseNode` or `CustomComponent`
- Auto-import from `src/frontend/src/` not relative paths crossing package boundaries
- API routes go in `src/backend/langflow/api/v1/` following FastAPI router pattern

## Tab Completion Preferences
- Python backend: use Pydantic v2 models (`model_validate` not `parse_obj`)
- TypeScript: prefer `interface` over `type` for component props, strict null checks
- Use `useQuery`/`useMutation` from TanStack Query for all API calls
- Flow state management: use `useFlowStore` (Zustand), never local React state for flow data

## Inline Edit Rules
- Adding a new component type: register in `src/backend/langflow/components/` + add frontend component in `src/frontend/src/components/`
- API endpoints must include OpenAPI docstrings (used for auto-generated docs)
- CSS: use Tailwind utility classes, no custom CSS files for new components
- Database changes: Alembic migration required, placed in `src/backend/langflow/alembic/versions/`

## Project-Specific Conventions
- Monorepo structure: `src/backend/` (FastAPI) + `src/frontend/` (React/Vite)
- Flow serialization: all flow data goes through `storeUtils.ts`
- Component parameters use `parameterUtils.ts` for dynamic form generation
- Testing: Playwright for E2E (`tests/`), Vitest for frontend, pytest for backend
